eateries.name: 104West!
eateries.about:
Located next to the Center for Jewish Living building on the south edge of west campus, 104West! is Cornell's kosher and multicultural dining room. Menus are prepared under the supervision of STAR-K (meat and pareve) and STAR-D (dairy) Kosher Certifications, and Jewish dietary laws are strictly followed with the direction of a resident "Mashgiach," or kosher-food supervisor.

You don't have to keep kosher to enjoy the menu–come sample traditional kosher entrees and enjoy mouth-watering ethnic and international options with a kosher flair. Dining options also include Halal, Seventh-day Adventist, vegetarian, vegan, and other diets.

Shabbat dinner times vary over the course of the year, based on sunset times. Save money and help us plan by making advance reservations for Shabbat dinners and holiday meals at https://kosher.scl.cornell.edu!

More Info: 104West!
eateries.aboutshort: Cornell's kosher and multicultural dining room is STAR-K and STAR-D certified.

eateries.name: McCormick's at Moakley House
eateries.about:
McCormick's at Moakley House offers a casual environment close to campus, open daily through the season. Treat a campus visitor to an impeccably served luncheon, stop for refreshments after a round of golf, meet coworkers at the end of the day for a burger and a beer, or bring the family for a relaxing weekend brunch. Named for Jack McCormick, a varsity golfer from the Cornell Class of 1957 whose will included a bequest to modernize Moakley House, this eatery alongside the award-winning Robert Trent Jones Golf Course at Cornell University isn't just for golfers. It's open to the public and has plenty of parking, and we welcome everyone for a drink, a snack, or a meal. McCormick's is closed for the 2021 season as of September 24th.

More Info: McCormick's at Moakley House
eateries.aboutshort: Named for Jack McCormick, a varsity golfer from the Cornell Class of 1957, McCormick's is open to the public and has plenty of parking.
